messages.text: Dad! Why didn‚Äôt you tell me that Cal was going to propose?
Hello to you, too. I‚Äôm fine, thanks for asking.
What about Cal?!
He asked me not to tell you.
I‚Äôm your DAUGHTER. Your flesh and blood‚Äî
We‚Äôre not supposed to keep secrets from one another.
He was heartbroken after you broke up with him. How could I go back on my word?
It would be like kicking a puppy‚Ä¶he was devastated.
He was?
Yes. You dumped him the day before he‚Äôd planned to surprise you with a balloon ride over your favorite lake‚Ä¶
The two of you were going to have a romantic picnic‚Ä¶
And then he was going to ask you to be his wife.
I think he even paid for a string quartet to play.
A balloon ride? String quartet?!
Yep. He lost all his deposits, too. Wasn‚Äôt cheap.
Not to mention the ring. He got it at Tiffany.
He DID?!
The diamond was a carat and a half!
I feel terrible. Why didn‚Äôt you warn me?
I did ‚Äî I told you not to break up with him.
Why didn‚Äôt I listen to you?
I ask myself that all the time.
Dad!
I‚Äôm kidding! I love you, sweetheart. You know that.
What‚Äôs this all about? How did you find out?
Cal and I got matched on Spark yesterday. We texted.
It‚Äôs fate! Told you that you two were meant to be together.
I‚Äôm getting my wedding binder out. That wedding planner is probably still taking new clients‚Ä¶
DAD! No.
Come on, I know you still have feelings for him.
I do not.
Then why do you care that he wanted to propose?
I just‚Ä¶feel bad.
Uh-huh. You know I can always tell when you‚Äôre lying.
Just like the time you told me you didn‚Äôt know what happened to the four boxes of Girl Scout cookies in the cabinet when you were four‚Ä¶
Even though your face was covered in chocolate.
I have a Thin Mint addiction. You know this.
#Truth
Please don‚Äôt use hashtags, Dad.
#DadsHip #DadKnowsBest #DadRules
DAD!
#JennStillLovesCal
NO! And, even if I DID have feelings for him‚Ä¶
He‚Äôs all fit and hot now ‚Äî so he has like, a million girls throwing themselves at him.
None of that matters. He still loves you.
You think?
I know. You didn‚Äôt see the boy after you crushed him‚Äî
I wasn‚Äôt sure he‚Äôd ever recover.
We‚Äôre going on a pizza date tonight.
Hmmm.
Hmmm? What does that mean?!
I love you. I love Cal. That‚Äôs why I don‚Äôt want to see either of you get hurt.
Stop! I thought you wanted us back together!
I do, but you have to be sure.
I tease you about the binder, but you have to do what‚Äôs right for you.
Cal‚Äôs a great guy, but if he‚Äôs not the guy for you, then you should walk away.
Thanks, Dad. But‚Ä¶I don‚Äôt know anymore.
Really?
Yes. I broke up with Cal because I was bored. I moved all the way out here to work for Ryde, but then all the scandals came along‚Ä¶
And now I don‚Äôt even know why I wanted this job in the first place!
I thought I‚Äôd go on all these dates, but I haven‚Äôt met anybody nearly as good as Cal, and my life is‚Ä¶
Well, just‚Ä¶not so good.
You tried something new. You wanted to advance your career by working for the next Uber‚Äî
There‚Äôs nothing wrong with that.
And you weren‚Äôt sure you wanted to settle down ‚Äî yet.
Nothing wrong with that, either.
I work in HR, Dad. I‚Äôm not even sure if this is what I want to do at all. My ‚Äúcareer‚Äù is a big headache.
And now I don‚Äôt have Cal‚Äî
What if I made a mistake?
Life is all about making mistakes. Remember that time I bought the motorcycle?
How could I forget?
You rode it once, crashed it after riding only ten feet in the cul de sac and never rode it again.
Exactly. #LifeLesson #LifeHasNoInstructionManual #AlsoRoadRashSeriouslyStings
More like ‚Äî Dad has a serious hashtag addiction and refuses help‚Ä¶
Anyway, what if life is giving me a second chance with Cal?
Maybe I should take it‚Ä¶
I love you. I want you to be happy. But, be sure of what you want‚Äî
Don‚Äôt break Cal‚Äôs heart again. Please.
How can I?
He probably doesn‚Äôt even care about me anymore.
He cares about you, trust me.
So be sure you don‚Äôt toy with him‚Äî
Sometimes that can happen by accident.
He‚Äôs got so many other girls in his life, Dad. Did you see the personal trainer he went out with?
Selena? Yeah, she‚Äôs pretty. But she‚Äôs no you.
DAD! You know about Selena?
Cal and I are Facebook friends.
I saw the pictures ‚Äî new girl on his arm nearly every weekend!
And he calls me sometimes. We talk. I give him advice‚Äî
He LIKES my hashtags.
Lord help us.
I give GREAT advice!
I know you do, Dad. So what would you tell me to do?
Follow your heart. Be yourself, everyone else is taken.
You only get one shot in life so don‚Äôt waste it. Love loud.
Are you just quoting the inspirational posters in your study?
Maybe. Oh, yeah ‚Äî there‚Äôs also, ‚ÄòHang in There.‚Äô
You‚Äôre ridiculous.
I think what you mean is awesome. So, when‚Äôs the date?
It was supposed to be five minutes ago. I‚Äôm waiting at the pizza place now.
Not like Cal to be late. He‚Äôs usually so punctual.
Do you think he stood me up?
Maybe he found a better date.
Better than you? Not possible.
What if I really messed it all up?
You haven‚Äôt messed anything up‚Äî
I‚Äôm proud of you and all that you‚Äôve done with your life, and that‚Äôs with or without Cal.
Thanks, Dad. I love you.
Love you, too.
Oh, wait. I think I see him coming!
